Huruma OCS Simon Ndeti is dead. Pangani deputy police boss William Sirego said the officer was discovered dead at the house in Huruma on Wednesday night. He lived alone. Sirego said the officer had earlier visited Nairobi West Hospital where he was treated and returned to his house. "The officer died yesterday night. He had earlier visited Nairobi West Hospital where he was treated and returned home. He was on drugs," Sirego told the Star on the phone on Thursday. Ndeti was recently transferred to the current posting from Karatina police station in Nyeri county, where he had served in the same capacity.